results.name: a(1) = 2; a(n+1) is the least prime p not already used such that p-a(n) is not equal to a(k+1)-a(k) for any k < n.
comment: Apparently a rearrangement of the primes. Among the first 10000 terms the only missing primes are prime(9530,9532,9533,9541,9552,9556,9557,9560,9562,9563,...) = (99259,99289,99317,99401,99559,99581,99607,99643,99667,99679,...). - _Zak Seidov_, Nov 18 2014
